adopt

void adopt(IAgent agent)
Registers an IAgent object as adopting this ITrait and any child traits. Increments the trait's adoption count, in a thread-safe way, along with the adoption count of any child traits.

Parameters:
agent - an IAgent object, representing the agent adopting this trait

unadopt

void unadopt(IAgent agent)
Unregisters an IAgent object from this trait and its child traits. Decrements the trait's adoption count, in a thread-safe way, along with the adoption count of any child traits.

Parameters:
agent - an IAgent object, representing the agent unregistering this trait

setOwningDimension

void setOwningDimension(ITraitDimension owningDimension)
Sets the ITraitDimension which "owns" this trait. Many simple models may not employ trait dimensions at all, since they are primarily useful in organizing "alternative" traits in models with multidimensional state spaces.

Parameters:
owningDimension -

clearAdoptionData

hasCompleteDuration

java.lang.Boolean hasCompleteDuration()
Returns true if the trait has zero adoptees and has been "lost" from the population, and thus a total duration can be calculated. If this returns false for a given trait, the caller should assume that the trait has a non-zero adoption count and thus is still "in play" within the population, so asking for its duration would skew any statistics.

getTraitDuration

java.lang.Integer getTraitDuration()
Returns the number of model ticks (copying events in Moran-style models, or N * tick copying events in WF models) the trait persisted in the population at non-zero adoption levels before the adoption count first hit zero.

Returns:
number of model ticks the trait persisted in the population before being lost
